snippet.textDisplay: This is the kalam of Shah Hussain Lahori (Punjabi: شاہ حسین‎). He was a 16th century Punjabi Sufi poet who is regarded as a pioneer of the Kafi form of Punjabi poetry. Hussain's love for a Hindu boy named "Madho" has resulted in them being referred to as a single person with the composite name of "Madho Lal Hussain".
